<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LINEBACKER NAZEL COMMITS TO USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC has received an oral commitment from
linebacker Omar Nazel of Oakland Skyline High. Nazel (6-foot-4, 220
pounds) selected the Trojans over Colorado, Washington, Arizona and
Cal. He had 14 sacks and 86 tackles for Skyline.
</P>
<P>
   Nazel is the fourth linebacker to commit to the Trojans, joining
Markus Steele (Long Beach City College), Aaron Graham (Bakersfield)
and Chris Prosser (San Diego Morse).
</P>
<P>
   USC now has 14 commitments and is waiting on approximately 17
players to make their final decisions.
</P>
<P>
   Rogers enrolls: Tight end Jacob Rogers of Oxnard High is
attending classes at USC and will be able to participate in spring
practice, which is expected to begin March 26. Rogers (6-6, 235)
graduated early from Oxnard and was the first player to commit to
USC when he announced his decision last spring.
</P>
<P>
   Williams arraigned: Defensive tackle Aaron Williams pleaded not
guilty in Orange Superior Court to prowling charges and for having
unpaid traffic tickets on Tuesday. Williams was arrested last month
in Costa Mesa.
</P>
<P>
   A pretrial hearing is set for Feb. 8, but Williams' attorney,
Bob Van Hoy, said he is discussing a plea bargain with the district
attorney's office.
</P>
<P>
   ``I believe there should be a dismissal,'' Van Hoy said.
</P>
</TEXT>
