<P>
   &UR; WELCOMES AND WORRIES: KING HUSSEIN RETURNS TO JORDAN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (TIMELY for Tuesday, 19 January) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Patrick Cockburn &QL;
</P>
<P>
   AMMAN _ Piloting his own plane, King Hussein returned to Jordan
today following six months of chemotherapy treatment for cancer in
the U.S. While Jordanians publicly celebrated his reported cure
from lymphoma, they privately speculated about who will succeed to
the throne the king has held for 45 years _ and about the future of
their country after his reign.
</P>
<P>
   The danger of succession from King Hussein's point of view is
that Jordan cannot afford a weak ruler because it is less poweful
than all of its neighbors. He knows his dynasty cannot afford to
make too many mistakes. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (750 words) &QL;
</P>
