<P>
   &UR; WE MUST INTERVENE IN KOSOVO &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Commentary) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By The Editorial Board of The Independent of London &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Serbian forces may have cleared the bodies from the mosque. They
may have succeeded in hiding some of the evidence from
international observers. But the implications of the massacre in
the Kosovo town of Racak cannot be cleaned up so easily, for the
anger felt around the world has been both heartfelt and genuine.
</P>
<P>
   If we do not wish to see more innocent people die in vain, the
only solution is to intervene in force to secure the separation of
the combatants in Kosovo and to hope that negotiation is forced by
the stalemate. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (650 words) &QL;
</P>
