r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN     01-20 0667
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DEREK HARPER TO JOIN LAKERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Every playground needs an adult to keep the kids
in line, and the Lakers just found theirs in Derek Harper.
</P>
<P>
   Harper, 37 years old and a veteran of 15 NBA seasons, will be
signed by the team as soon as the lockout is lifted. His mere
arrival should be a positive influence on a team that is as young
as it is talented.
</P>
<P>
   Even the Lakers themselves, acknowledging their youth, had
frequently listed veteran experience as a primary need.
</P>
<P>
   Harper also gives the Lakers depth at point guard, where
experience was the most lacking. He joins third-year veteran Derek
Fisher and rookie Tyronn Lue.
</P>
<P>
   ``We like Derek Fisher a lot. We think he's a very, very good
player.... We really like our young kid (Lue),'' Lakers executive
Jerry West said. ``But I think when you have a veteran, you always
feel a little more comfortable that if things get tough, maybe he
might be better in a particular situation than a younger kid. We
also think he'll be a very steadying influence on some of our
people.''
</P>
<P>
   More than just a longtime veteran, Harper comes with a nice
resume: 90 playoff games, including a Finals appearance with the
New York Knicks in 1994. He's several years past his NBA
All-Defensive team honors (in 1987 and '90), but Harper's work on
that end of the floor was a main consideration.
</P>
<P>
   At 6-foot-4, Harper also has the height to defend against taller
Western Conference point guards, specifically Seattle's Gary Payton
and Phoenix's Jason Kidd. Fisher and Lue both stand closer to 6
feet.
</P>
<P>
   ``We think defensively he can handle most guards out there,''
West said.
</P>
<P>
   Fisher, who took over the starting job in place of an injured
Nick Van Exel last season and led the Lakers into the conference
finals, welcomed the addition of Harper _ even if it means moving
to the bench.
</P>
<P>
   ``As young as I am, getting a chance to play with or behind, or
however the arrangement will be, with somebody like Derek can only
help me individually,'' said Fisher, who called Harper ``one of the
classiest'' players in the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we need something like that on our team, especially
someone with as much experience as probably about five of our
(players) combined,'' he added. ``I'm going to be like a student in
a classroom, just listening to everything he says, picking up on
the little things he does in practice.''
</P>
<P>
   Who starts and who finishes games will be decided in training
camp, coach Del Harris said.
</P>
<P>
   Harper will sign a deal that falls under the minimum-salary
exception, which does not count against the salary cap. Under the
new veteran's salary scale, and as a player with more than 10
years, he will be earn $1 million.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers also pursued veteran Kevin Johnson but would have had
to use the $1.75-million, middle-class salary exception to sign
him. West is reserving that exception for free agent Rick Fox, whom
the Lakers hope to re-sign.
</P>
<P>
   Fox is entertaining more lucrative offers elsewhere but is still
strongly interested in the Lakers. He could make a decision as soon
as today.
</P>
<P>
   West also confirmed the Lakers will reacquire forward Travis
Knight from Boston, in exchange for forward Tony Battie.
</P>
<P>
   No transactions are official until the lockout is lifted,
sometime in the next day or two.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers continue to mull possible deals for a power forward,
using Elden Campbell as trade bait. Minnesota's Tom Gugliotta,
Sacramento's Chris Webber and Orlando's Horace Grant are still
being rumored as possibilities.
</P>
<P>
   ``It'd be nice if you had a perfect team, and we try to do the
best we can here,'' West said. ``To say that we don't have an
interest in doing something else would be a terrible lie. But we
are trying to do some other things. If we would get somebody else,
we'd feel good about it, but to say we're close to something would
be false also.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
