<P>
   COXNET FOOD _ FOOD 0115 _ If your New Year's resolution included
eating healthy and losing weight, you probably put Tex-Mex food on
the ``red light'' list. No more nachos nuked in the microwave. No
more Friday lunches at the cantina with the gang from work. But
everyone knows today's deprivation is likely to be tomorrow's
binge. So we have a better plan. Go ahead and dine on some
favorites, such as guacamole and enchiladas, but use lighter
recipes that are loaded with flavor, not fat. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
