<P>
   PIE-THROWERS (San Francisco) _ When it came to pie crimes and
misdemeanors, jurors in the Mayor Willie Brown pie-smearing trial
returned a bittersweet verdict: The panel convicted three activists
of battery, but acquitted them of the more serious charge of
assaulting a public official. By MACKENZIE WARREN.
</P>
<P>
   NAVY-DEPARTS (Concord, Calif. _ The Navy, once the dominant
military presence in the San Francisco Bay Area, will fold its
sails here later this year, turning the Concord Naval Weapons
Station, its last base in the region, over to the Army. By LARRY D.
HATFIELD.
</P>
