<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `Damage' wreaks classy havoc
 &HT;    By Eleanor Ringel
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Before Juliette Binoche was ``Oscar winner Juliette Binoche''
(for ``The English Patient''), she glowed opposite Jeremy Irons in
``Damage,'' a steamy but classy tale of a conservative politician
who risks his career and his marriage when he becomes sexually
besotted with his son's new girlfriend. An artful application of
cool gloss to raw acts of betrayal and passion, the movie burns
like dry ice. Now, here's the bonus: The DVD version offers both
the unrated and the R-rated cut. Plus an interview with the
director, the late Louis Malle.
</P>
<P>
   Eleanor Ringel writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
