</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RODALE'S-HEALTHY-LIVING-BUDGET-NYTSF </SLUG>
  
 (PLEASE NOTE: This budget has been transmitted three times _ into
the ``v'' advisory, ``l'' lifestyle news and ``a'' general news
files.)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; ATTENTION EDITORS: &LR;  The following is the budget for Rodale's
Healthy Living stories for release the week of Mon., Jan. 25. These
articles are free to Rodale Healthy Living clients. They can be
purchased individually by non-clients. To purchase a story or for
information on how to subscribe to Rodale's Healthy Living, call
(888) 269-8796.
</P>
<P>
   Photos are available on Wieck, Newscom or through e-mail.
</P>
<P>
   1. THE NEW WAY TO STOP A HEART ATTACK. From Prevention with art.
It takes more than diet and exercise to prevent a heart attack.
Here, what you need to know. (slugged: BC-RODALE-COVER-NYTSF).
</P>
<P>
   2. HEALTH BRIEFS. From Prevention with art. Stop cravings with
sunshine; working moms take care of themselves too; to ease asthma,
treat heartburn; lower blood pressure with magnesium. (slugged:
BC-RODALE-BRIEFS-NYTSF).
</P>
<P>
   3. HEALTHY EATING: FOODS THAT FIGHT FAT. From Prevention with
art. Here, a convenient guide to the tastiest, lowest-calorie,
reduced-fat choices at your supermarket. (slugged:
BC-HEALTHY-EATING-NYTSF).
</P>
<P>
   4. KEEPING FIT: WALKING FIT. From Prevention with art. Burn 50
percent more calories; walk away knee pain; walking partnerships
keep hearts healthy. (slugged: BC-RODALE-KEEPING-FIT-NYTSF).
</P>
<P>
   5. ASK THE DOCTOR. From Prevention. Questions on cervical
dysplasia and progesterone-only birth control pills. (slugged:
BC-RODALE-Q&AMP;A-NYTSF).
</P>
<P>
   6. HEALTHY PARENTING: PROTECT COMPUTER WIZARDS FROM JOINT
PROBLEMS. From Prevention. Here, tips on how to protect your kids
from carpal tunnel syndrome. (slugged:
BC-RODALE-HEALTHY-PARENTING-NYTSF).
 &UR; -0- &QL;
</P>
