<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
. 
The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Jimmy
Johnson at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
SIGHT-MOVIE (Los Angeles) _ Imagine how tough it was to make a
movie like ``At First Sight,'' the film that examines the difficult
relationship between a New York architect played by Mira Sorvino
and Val Kilmer as a blindmasseur who temporarily regains his sight.
Falling in love without the requisite longing gazes into one
another's eyes was quite the acting challenge _ for Val Kilmer
anyway. By Bob Strauss. 
. 
TURKS-TV (Los Angeles) _ If you watch tonight's premiere of
``Turks,'' you are more than likely to have this reaction:
``Haven't I seen this before?'' The CBS police drama about a
Chicago family is predictable and often cookie-cutter. But don't be
surprised if your second thought is: ``This isn't half-bad.'' By
Keith Marder. 
. 
TALKIN-RADIO (Los Angeles) _ Three Spanish-language stations took
the top places in the latest quarterly ratings, illustrating the
continued dominance of Spanish programming in Los Angeles. By Fred
Shuster.
<TEXT>
<P>
   . &QL;
</P>
