<P>
   SCI-FIBER-CANCER (Undated) _ The largest study ever to examine
the protective value of a high-fiber diet has found that when it
comes to preventing colon cancer, eating foods high in fiber does
not do any good. The study and an accompanying editorial will
appear in Thursday's New England Journal of Medicine. By Sheryl Gay
Stolberg. (800 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-ASTRO-DELAY (Washington) _ The launch of a $1 billion X-ray
astronomy satellite has been delayed at least five weeks from its
scheduled April 8 date, because the maker has discovered that the
circuit boards are debonding and may have to be rebuilt. The delay
may ripple through the year, playing havoc with the shuttle launch
schedule, which is organized around the space station. By Warren E.
Leary. (700 words)
</P>
