denies that confession. As Cambodia and the outside world prepare
for the possibility of trials for perhaps a dozen top Khmer Rouge
leaders, a large unanswered _ and generally unasked _ question is
how to deal with, or even how to think of, the people who actually
took part in the torture and the killing. By Seth Mydans.
