<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LITERARY QUIZ
</P>
<P>
   Edgar Allan Poe (1809-1849), poet and purveyor of tales of the
grotesque, is the subject this week. Here are 16 of the master's
tales, for which you must complete the titles by supplying the
correct missing word for each one. If you know your Poe, this one's
a keeper. You pass with nine correct answers (a simple majority)
but must have 14 right (!) to earn an A. Answers are on the
opposite page.
</P>
