</P>
<P>
   SUPER BOWL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS _ Talking to Falcons coach Dan Reeves about the
uncomfortable situation he left behind when he was fired as coach
of the Denver Broncos, where current Denver coach/former Reeves
assistant Mike Shanahan and QB John Elway are said to have
conspired against him. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-NOTES _ Falcons notebook. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FBN-MIAMI-PROFILE _ MIAMI _ Miami Vice, Scarface, stunning
beaches, cocaine kingpins, fire-breathing Cuban exiles, drop-dead
fashion models, riot-torn neighborhoods, crime novelists, corrupt
politicians, Santeria priests, slain tourists and assassinated
fashion designers: these are just a few of Miami is incarnations
during the past two decades. Two high-profile tourist murders this
weekend have put the tourism business on edge again. What will
Falcons fans find when they visit Miami for the Super Bowl? A
little of all of these, plus glorious January weather perfect for
cruising in a convertible. Just don't cut anybody off in traffic or
take the wrong exit off the freeway: you may face uzzi-toting road
ragers or tourist-targeting bad guys. We profile the city with all
its warts and still-shimmering magic. (M.WIlliams, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-BISHER-COLUMN _ Furman Bisher cwrites about the Falcons'
lesser know players. (Bisher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FBN-BRADLEY-COLUMN _ Mark Bradley column: Enjoy it now . . . if
Falcons' success continues, we'll soon be as jaded about them as we
are about the Braves. (Bradley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGE FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   FBC-RECRUIT-NOTES _ College football recruiting notebook.
(Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-PROBEUPDATE _ Former Atlanta Olympics chief Billy Payne,
saying ACOG people have nothing to hide, asks that if one of the
investigative bodies wishes to look at Atlanta's bid, let's do it
and get it over with. (Turner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-MARLINS-HENRY _ John Henry officially introduced as new
owner of the Marlins. So what's he going to do about a stadium?
(Capozzi, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BBN-MARLINS-FUTURE _ John Henry's views on the Marlins:
personnel, payroll, future, etc. (Graziano, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   BBN-STODA-COLUMN _ Column from Marlins/John Henry news
conference. (Stoda, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   .
</P>
<P>
   HOCKEY
</P>
<P>
   HKN-PANTHERS-BURE _ Pavel Bure joins the Panthers in New York,
just the place to cause a media frenzy. (Biggane, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   NBA
</P>
<P>
   BKN-HEAT _ Whatever news develops in Heat land. When will
training camps open? Anything more on Sprewell? John Starks coming
to Miami? (D'Angelo, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   BKN-HAWKS _ Christian Laettner signs with Detroit, officially
finishing his Hawks days. Plus, other Hawks developments. (Denberg,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   OUTDOORS
</P>
<P>
   OUTDOORS-NOTES _ Outdoor notebook. (Mitchell/Bernarde, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
