<HEADER>
A1450 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-KINKADE-LA-Z-BOY-TEX     01-20 0350
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KINKADE-LA-Z-BOY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A MARRIAGE MADE IN DOUBLE-WIDE HEAVEN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GAILE ROBINSON 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Thomas Kinkade is a painter of treacly landscapes who has a
nationwide string of galleries. He is the self-proclaimed ``Painter
of Light,'' whose work appeals to people with little formal art
training.
</P>
<P>
   La-Z-Boy is the largest manufacturer of upholstered furniture
sold in the United States. Its trademark chairs and sofas that flip
up, lean back and plug in are known as ``motion furniture'' and are
popular among those who watch a lot of television.
</P>
<P>
   Kinkade and La-Z-Boy found each other. The pairing, with a
profound marketing resonance, was announced in midsummer to snorts
of derision and mutterings of ``how perfect.''
</P>
<P>
   Time passed; then the press kit arrived.
</P>
<P>
   Squirming in anticipation and poised to snigger, we were
disappointed. The moment was squelched. The Thomas Kinkade Home
Furnishings Collection was not half-bad. It was more decent than
horrible.
</P>
<P>
   There are tapestries inspired by Kinkade's most saccharine,
shimmering paintings, such as ``Eiffel Tower'' and ``Victorian
Garden.'' The heavy case goods _ chests and armoires _ are carved
with his signature ``N,'' a symbol for his wife Nanette that is
hidden, at least once, in all his paintings.
</P>
<P>
   There is even a damask fabric that is an all-over ``N'' design.
</P>
<P>
   It sounds so ghastly _ the Eiffel Tower, the hidden ``N'' _ and
the news release reads even worse. ``Sink into the comfort and
warmth of a Thomas Kinkade painting with La-Z-Boy's new Gatsby
sofa.'' Or what about this: ``These fabrics reflect our
interpretation of the types of patterns one might find inside the
homes depicted in Thomas Kinkade's paintings.''
</P>
<P>
   If only the furniture actually measured up, er, down to its
potential. The actuality, though, is soft, pretty fabrics and
decent furniture with classic shapes and nice proportions.
</P>
<P>
   Drat _ left choking on an unrequited snigger.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
