economy's recent strong performance.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street generally reacted positively to Greenspan as he
signaled that the Federal Reserve wasn't likely to change interest
rates any time soon.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones industrial average was up more than 75 points
after Greenspan's remarks but ultimately closed down 19.31 points
to 9,335.91. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 rose 4.61 to 1,256.61, and
the Nasdaq composite index rose 7.32 to 2,415.49.
</P>
</TEXT>
