<SLUG> BC-BEST-TECHTOWNS21-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Atlanta ranks No. 3 on best place for high-tech workers,
magazine says
 &HT;    By Tammy Joyner
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service ATLANTA _ Atlanta is the third best
<TEXT>
place in America for information technology workers, according to
Computerworld magazine's annual ranking.
<P>
   ``It's booming with industry, growth and jobs, jobs, jobs,'' the
magazine said of Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   The growth of technical support, help desk and response centers
and consulting firms in the metro area has created huge demands for
systems integrators, systems consultants, client/server software
developers and Internet and networking experts, the review said.
</P>
<P>
   And professionals in those kinds of jobs are commanding top
salary. Annual salary for a senior systems analyst in Atlanta?
About $75,000 to $80,000 in a town where the cost of living is
relatively low.
</P>
<P>
   Boston, with its plethora of universities such as Harvard and
MIT, was the best place for IT workers who can basically call their
own shots. Chicago ranked second.
</P>
<P>
   T E C H T O W N S
</P>
<P>
   Best cities for high tech job seekers:
</P>
<P>
   1. Boston
</P>
<P>
   2. Chicago
</P>
<P>
   3. Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   4. Washington
</P>
<P>
   5. New York
</P>
<P>
   6. San Francisco
</P>
<P>
   7. Seattle
</P>
<P>
   8. Las Vegas
</P>
<P>
   9. St. Louis
</P>
<P>
   10. Austin, Tex.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
