<P>
   DEFENSE-MISSILE (Washington) _ The Pentagon announced Wednesday
that the threat of a ballistic missile strike from enemy nations
like North Korea or Iran now justified building a limited national
missile defense system, despite prohibitions in the Anti-Ballistic
Missile treaty with Russia. Defense Secretary William Cohen said
that while the United States would commence negotiations with
Russia to amend the 1972 treaty, he would not rule out unilaterally
withdrawing from the treaty if negotiators could not find a way to
permit a limited national missile defense system. By Steven Lee
Myers.
