   Off-lead story:
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) _ A White House lawyer on Wednesday
dismissed the charge that President Clinton lied before a grand
jury as nothing more than ``arguments over semantics'' and accused
House Republicans of drawing conclusions more extreme than those of
Kenneth Starr. ``It is hard to take the charges seriously,'' the
White House special counsel, Gregory Craig, told the senators on
the second day of defense arguments. By R.W. Apple Jr.
</P>
