   FOLD
</P>
<P>
   STATEOFUNION-CLINTON (Buffalo, N.Y.) - An exuberant President
Clinton, showing no signs of the weight of impeachment, starred in
a foot-stomping rally on Wednesday, where he amplified the themes
of his State of the Union address and attacked Republican proposals
for across-the-board tax cuts. By John M. Broder. Under a
three-colum photo at the top of the page.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move the story by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
