   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; PACBELL _  &LR; Pacific Bell said yesterday that it canceled its
contract with a telemarketing firm that was misleading customers
about Caller ID blocking, and will call back everyone who got the
telemarketing pitch to see whether they have the service they want.
</P>
<P>
   The phone company terminated the contract after learning that
Business Response Inc. of St. Louis was doing things ``that
shouldn't have been done,'' Pac Bell spokesman John Britton said.
By Deborah Solomon
