 &UR; PERSONAL TECH PACKAGE &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; ESCRIP &LR;  _ It's a familiar sight to any parent of a school-aged
child: A card table set up outside the cafeteria with PTA
volunteers selling scrip _ gift certificates to Safeway, Lucky's,
Macy's, Costco, Target and other stores _ as a fund-raiser.
</P>
<P>
   Now a San Mateo startup hopes to turn scrip sales into an
all-electronic transaction, eliminating the need for card tables,
paper certificates and volunteer time. By Carolyn Said
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMPUTING _  &LR; Question: My wife just got a new computer, so now
we're a two-computer household. The PCs are in different rooms. Is
there a simple way to link them so that we can easily move files
back and forth? How about a way that I can use her high-speed
modem? Columnist David Einstein has the answer.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-20-99 2126EST &QL; 
