<P>
   The following Arizona Republic stories have been added for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for Thursday, Jan. 21. If
you have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at
(602) 271-8108.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
AMWEST _ America West Airlines, the hometown carrier that soared
into the airline major leagues, went bankrupt and prospered again,
is being pursued by United Airlines. Story will move in the ``A''
and ``F'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
IMPACT _ How would life in the Phoenix area change with if America
West Airlines merges with United Airlines? Story will move in the
``F'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
EARNS _ America West Airlines, knocked off course in 1998 by labor
battles, chronic flight delays and a $5 million FAA fine over
maintenance violations, still managed to report record net income
of $108.6 million for the year. Story will move in the ``F''
category. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   EMPLOYEES _ America West Airlines employees, some still stinging
from tense union negotiations, cheered a possible United Airlines
buyout that they said would bring them higher pay. That is, if
United keeps them on the payroll. Story will move in the ``F''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
INDUSTRY _ After a lengthy hiatus, airline mergers are making a
comeback. Dallas-based American Airlines broke the ice in November
with its announced acquisition of Nevada's Reno Air Inc. And now,
Chicago's United Airlines has confirmed an interest in acquiring
Tempe-based America West Airlines. Story will move in the ``F''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
NICKELL-COL _ The rumors had been around before. America West is
going to merge with (fill in the blank). America West is going to
be bought by (fill in the blank). But those never seemed to be more
than someone's fantasy. This time it was different. Story will move
in the ``F'' category. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
